      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "From a purely moral standpoint, prioritizing human life often carries significant weight, suggesting a strong argument for healthcare as a right. Many ethical frameworks support the idea that basic survival needs supersede market logic. However, the counterargument holds that excessive bureaucracy can *negatively* impact the quality and speed of care, which also threatens life. It becomes a balance between ensuring access and maintaining an effective, responsive system.",
