      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like the \"bureaucracy\" argument is just a way to avoid the real issue. if we agree that people shouldn't die because they're poor, isn't the debate basically over? like, if a policy is morally right, shouldn't we just make it a reality regardless of whether it's \"efficient\" by capitalist standards?",
